cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about a weakly-supervised semantic segmentation framework that uses a deconvolutional neural network. The main application of this framework is in medical image analysis, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of feature extraction and stacking, which are common techniques in machine learning and could place it in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of convolutional and deconvolutional operations, which are common in deep learning and could place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The use of neural networks and the focus on performance could also suggest the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of medical images, which could suggest the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
